                                                    1.5.2.	You may indicate your preferred notification channels (e.g. Email and/or SMS).  For Payment Reminders, You will always receive email notifications. Subscribers of Paperless Billing will always receive Billing Notifications via email.
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                    
                                                    1.5.3.	If You have not received any messages from MERALCO, please check Your Spam, Bulk, or Junk folders and add MERALCO as one of Your approved senders list.
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                </div>
                                                
                                                1.6.	<b>SEARCH</b>
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                As a user of the MERALCO Online, You will be able to utilize its search function.
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                1.7.	<b>DASHBOARD FOR CONGLOMERATE MERALCO Online ACCOUNTS</b>
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                The conglomerate dashboard allows You to view the summary details for the electric services enrolled under the Conglomerate account such as, but not limited to, balance from previous billing, billed amount for the month, payments made and outstanding balances.
                                                <br /><br />
                                            </div>
                                            
                                            <b>2.	NON-MERALCO Online (but Website) USERS</b>
                                            <br /><br />
                                            
                                            <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                2.1.	<b>SERVICE APPLICATION - Applying as a Business Entity / Contractor / Representative</b>
                                                <br /><br />
                                                As a Non-MERALCO Online (but Website) User, You may:
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                    2.1.1.	Apply for: (i) New Electric Service; (ii) Modification of Service; (iii) Transfer of Service; and (iv) Termination of Service. You would need to fill out and submit all applicable online forms. A reference number will be provided to You upon completion every application;
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                    
                                                    2.1.2.	Track Your application using the reference number;
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                    
                                                    2.1.3.	Upload or attach documents in support of your application;
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                    
                                                    2.1.4.	Receive notifications and updates regarding Your service application through different channels such as Email or SMS.
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                </div>
                                                
                                                2.2.	<b>ONLINE PAYMENTS – PAY AS A GUEST</b>
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                As a Non-MERALCO Online (but Website) User, You may pay Your bill online through the Website using a credit card, debit card, Prepaid Card (Smart Money, Paymaya, Gcash), and other available payment channels subject to the following:
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                    2.2.1.	 Pay your bills through the Website using a credit card, debit card, Prepaid Card (Smart Money, Paymaya, Gcash) and other available payment channels subject to the following:
                                                    <br /><br />
                                                    
                                                    <div class="slds-m-eft_medium">
                                                        2.2.1.1.	<b>PAYMENT OF CONVENIENCE FEE</b>
                                                        <br /><br />
                                                        
                                                        <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                            2.2.1.1.1.	Convenience Fee is a charge imposed by MERALCO's Payment Gateway Partner as payment for the processing of online payments. This Fee is charged directly by our Payment Gateway Partner and in no case shall this fee be credited to MERALCO.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            
                                                            2.2.1.1.2.	The rate of the Convenience Fee is dependent on the payment option You select, as follows:
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            
                                                            <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                                2.2.1.1.2.1.	For payments using Credit Card and Debit Card under Visa, Mastercard, or JCB, and Prepaid Card through GCash: 1.25% of the Amount of Your electric bill payment.
                                                                <br /><br />
                                                                2.2.1.1.2.2.	For payments using E-wallet through PayPal: 1.50% of the Amount of Your electric bill payment.
                                                                <br /><br />
                                                                2.2.1.1.2.3.	For payments using Debit Card under Bancnet and Prepaid Card through PayMaya, and SmartMoney: 0% of the Amount of Your electric bill payment.
                                                                <br /><br />
                                                            </div>
                                                            
                                                            2.2.1.1.3.	The Convenience Fee shall be on top of Your electric bill payment.  This will be shown in the Payment Summary screen, before You complete your payment transaction.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                        </div>
                                                        
                                                        2.2.1.2.	<b>PAYMENT PROCESSING AND CUT-OFF TIME</b>
                                                        <br /><br />
                                                        <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                            2.2.1.2.1.	Payments made via the MERALCO Online will be processed daily, Mondays – Fridays, 7:00AM – 11:00PM (PHT).  Payments made past 11:00PM (PHT), will be processed and posted 7:00AM (PHT) the next day.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.2.2.	Your online payment shall be applied to the specific bill/s selected for settlement; unless said bills have already been paid through a different channel (other than through the Website and MERALCO Online), in which case, Your online payment will be applied to any other outstanding bills under Your account, if there is any, or will be treated as advance payment (in case there are no any other outstanding bills).
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.2.3.	Advance payment and overpayment will be applied to the next succeeding electric bills of Your selected electric service account. There is “overpayment” if the amount paid is more than the total amount of all outstanding bills for all enrolled electric service accounts. There is an “advance payment” if You pay any amount even if there are no outstanding bills for all Your enrolled electric service accounts.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.2.4.	Partial payment can be made if one specific bill is selected for payment. A partially paid bill can still trigger service disconnection if full payment is not made by due date.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.2.5.	Payment credentials that will be provided will not be saved by MERALCO and will only be sent to the Payment Gateway to facilitate payment processing.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                        </div>
                                                        
                                                        2.2.1.3.	<b>DISCONNECTION AND RECONNECTION</b>
                                                        <br /><br />
                                                        
                                                        <div class="slds-m-left_medium">
                                                            2.2.1.3.1.	Failure to settle outstanding bill/s in full on or before the due date shall result to service disconnection.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.3.2.	For electric services pending disconnection at the time of payment processing, disconnection may still occur even with the settlement of bills   and, should disconnection occur, the subject electric service will be reconnected following the same handling for services disconnected but not yet terminated at point of payment.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.3.3.	For electric services already disconnected at the time of payment processing, reconnection will be within 24 hours from MERALCO's receipt of actual payment, i.e. first applicable banking day. The applicable Reconnection Fee shall be charged to the next bill.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                            2.2.1.3.4.	For disconnected electric services that are already terminated at the time of payment processing the reconnection of electric services shall be effected after the submission of required documents and payment of required service deposit.
                                                            <br /><br />
                                                        </div>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                                
                                                2.3.	<b>SEARCH</b>
                                                <br /><br />
                                                
                                                As a Non-MERALCO Online (but Website) User, You may utilize the search function of the Website.
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <!---->
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            
                        </div>
